  "rationale": "<p>If <i>m</i> &minus; <i>y</i> is a factor of the polynomial, then substituting <i>y</i> = <i>m</i> makes the expression equal to 0. This gives &minus;<i>m</i>&sup2; + (1/37)<i>n</i><i>m</i>&sup2; = 0. Factoring out <i>m</i>&sup2; and using <i>m</i> &gt; 0 gives &minus;1 + <i>n</i>/37 = 0, so <i>n</i> = 37. The other choices come from sign errors or omitting the factor of 37.</p>",
